-- Colombian Stock Movers: Ecopetrol, Canacol Gain; ETB Declines
-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 2012-01-13T21:47:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-13/colombian-stock-movers-ecopetrol-canacol-gain-etb-declines.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. local time.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  gained 0.3 percent to 13,123.86, while the
Colcap Index rose 0.4 percent to 1,592.82.  Oil companies  gained after Colombia’s Minister of Energy
and Mines Mauricio Cardenas said total production of all oil
companies operating in Colombia will rise to an average of 1.1
million barrels a day in December 2012 from 930,000 barrels a
day last year.  Canacol Energy Ltd. (CNEC)  , the Calgary-based  oil
company  that operates fields in Colombia, rose 1.3 percent to
1,590 pesos.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  , Colombia’s biggest oil company,
gained 3.7 percent to 4,480 pesos.  Empresa de Telecomunicaciones de Bogota SA  (ETB CB), the
city-run phone company serving Colombia’s capital, fell 3
percent to 518 pesos after yesterday’s 10 percent surge was
overdone, said Juan David Pineros, analyst at Bogota-based
brokerage Interbolsa SA.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
